race.comment: CURADO (3) struggled to see the 1400m out when eighth over 1400m at Warwick Farm with the 58kg. Gets map favours today back to the 1200m and the winkers come off. Ready to break through. BRITISH NAVY (2) not that far away on debut when sixth over 1000m at Nowra. Desperate for this trip and further now and expected to be very competitive. CONICAL NET (11) unwanted in betting on resumption and ran accordingly when eleventh over 1200m at Randwick. Showed ability last campaign and will find this more to her liking. BELLARATA (8) heavily supported at debut when showed good early speed before being swamped late to finish sixth over 1280m at Muswellbrook. Will come on greatly with the run and deserves another chance from the better draw.
